class Solution {
    public int largestRectangleArea(int[] heigths) {
        int[] lsei = new int[heigths.length];
        int[] psei = new int[heigths.length];

        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();

        for(int i=0; i<heigths.length; i++){
            lsei[i] = heigths.length;
            psei[i] = 0;
        }

        for(int i=0; i<heigths.length; i++){
            while(true){
                if(stack.isEmpty()){
                    stack.push(i);
                    break;
                }
                int idx = stack.peek();
                if(heigths[i] < heigths[idx]){
                    lsei[idx] = i;
                    stack.pop();
                } else {
                    stack.push(i);
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        while(!stack.isEmpty()){
            lsei[stack.pop()] = heigths.length;
        }

        stack.clear();

        for(int i=heigths.length-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(true){
                if(stack.isEmpty()){
                    stack.push(i);
                    break;
                }
                int idx = stack.peek();
                if(heigths[i] <= heigths[idx]){
                    psei[idx] = i;
                    stack.pop();
                } else {
                    stack.push(i);
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        while(!stack.isEmpty()){
            psei[stack.pop()] = -1;
        }

        int max = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<heigths.length; i++){
            max = Math.max(max, heigths[i] * (lsei[i] - psei[i] -1));
        }
        return max;
    }
}




You are given an array heights, where each element represents the height of a bar in a histogram. Each bar has a width of 1.

Your task is to find the largest rectangular area that can be formed using one or more consecutive bars in the histogram.

Example 1

Input:

heights = [2,1,5,6,2,3]

Output:

10

Explanation:

The largest rectangle is formed using the bars with heights 5 and 6.
Width = 2
Height = 5 (the smaller of the two)
Area = 5 × 2 = 10
Example 2

Input:

heights = [2,4]

Output:

4
Constraints
1 <= heights.length <= 10^5
0 <= heights[i] <= 10^4
Idea

For each bar:

Find the Previous Smaller Element (PSE).
Find the Next Smaller Element (NSE).
The current bar can extend from the previous smaller bar to the next smaller bar.

The width of the largest rectangle using the current bar is:

width = NSE - PSE - 1

The area is:

area = heights[i] × width

The optimal solution uses a monotonic increasing stack and runs in:

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)
